    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>States a people is a tributary to a suzerain ruler, or in more recent history, to a more powerful state that controls its foreign affairs while allowing the tributary vassal state some limited domestic autonomy. An historical example is the Ottoman Empire and its surrounding regions. </Note_Text>
